## Prerequisites
- Docker 24+, Docker Compose v2
- Terraform 1.5+
- Azure CLI 2.50+
- kubectl 1.30+
- Azure Subscription with Contributor role

## 1. Local Development

cp .env.example .env
docker compose build
docker compose up -d

| Service  | URL                          |
|----------|------------------------------|
| Frontend | http://localhost:8080        |
| Backend  | http://localhost:8000/health |
| Swagger  | http://localhost:8000/docs   |

## 2. Provision Azure Infrastructure

# One-time: create remote state storage (see deployment-guide.md)

cd terraform
terraform init
terraform plan -var-file=environments/dev.tfvars -out=tfplan
terraform apply tfplan
terraform output

az aks get-credentials -g hydrus-dev-rg -n hydrus-dev-aks --overwrite-existing
kubectl get nodes

## 3. Install Ingress Controller

helm repo add ingress-nginx https://kubernetes.github.io/ingress-nginx
helm install ingress-nginx ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx \
    --namespace ingress-nginx --create-namespace

## 4. Deploy

Deploy is automated via `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` on push to `main`.
Manual deploy:

kubectl apply -f k8s/

## 5. Monitoring

helm install monitoring prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
    --namespace monitoring --create-namespace

See `docs/monitoring-plan.md`.

## 6. Cleanup

kubectl delete -f k8s/
terraform destroy -var-file=environments/dev.tfvars

